{
  "stem": "19198.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was made very clear that we could go only with our family's approval.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The business was still functioning.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "People who shopped there knew that they were exposing themselves to insult from the-- from the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Many who-- certainly nobody who worked for that [NON-ENGLISH], the major industry, would dare to buy in the Jewish store.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But there were still people who had the guts to buy from Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But that number decreased constantly, and the threats against them were constant.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, what I've mentioned a moment ago certainly changed the lifestyle of most Jews who were still employed.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The immediate changes, that came within-- in some cases, within days, sometimes within weeks or months of the Nazis taking over, is that anybody in public employ was fired.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The-- anybody who was-- who had public visibility, actors for instance, and theaters, most of which were publicly supported theaters, they were fired The-- in-- in some of the occupations, they lost their jobs.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So the-- the lives of those people changed almost immediately.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The reaction of the Jewish community was dramatic, in that within a-- a few months, there were Jewish organizations that just hadn't existed before.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Welfare organizations, because they-- you had to take care of people who had lost their income.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Cultural organizations, the-- for instance, in-- in Heidelberg, which had a Jewish community of maybe 200 or 300 families, we started a little theater group.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I played the-- the lead in a performance of 'Jacob's Dream' by Beer-Hofmann, a play which had been performed in Germany, but, of course, could not be performed anymore, because Beer-Hofmann was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The Jewish orchestras were formed, et cetera, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The-- the Jewish response to being isolated from the rest of the community was a very constructive and creative response.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
